		<div id="comment_body_64302327"><p><div class="quote"><p>It lets you decorate any website as if it wasn't running in a browser.</p><p>"Progressive web apps" are neither apps nor progressive: they're a phenomenally inefficient of running an application with zero control over the application, that the lazy computer users of today like because they don't have to install them.</p></div><p>When users today want to argue that they&rsquo;re NOT &ldquo;lazy&rdquo;, I&rsquo;m reminded of the fact that the install wizards that drove setup.exe, was <i>already</i> the lazy and easy way of installing things.  And we were forced to do better.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64302327">

</div>
</div>

